    "summary": "a small hosted memory layer for AI agents",
    "body": "Most AI agent workflows lose useful context between sessions, tools, and chats. The usual fixes are either too manual, like copying notes into docs, or too heavy, like setting up a database, vector store, or custom RAG stack. pumaDB gives agents a simple shared place to save and reuse notes, facts, preferences, project context, transcripts, task state, and other useful memory. No database setup, vector DB, or infrastructure to manage",
